8-18. Three mythical examples of the effect of supplication. Tele- phus, King of the Mysians, was wounded by Achilles when the Greeks landed at Troy. His wound would not heal‚ and he was finally forced to come as a suppliant to his enemy, in accordance with an oracle which said he could be cured only by the rust of the spear that had struck him.
